<dl id="n15001i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15001i">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15001i"> 1(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hastening his steps / &amp; smiling</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&ldquo;Hysterical Phantasies and Their Relation to Bisexuality&rdquo;]</font>: It is easy to recognize a daydreamer in the street, however, by his sudden absentminded <mark>smile</mark>, his way of talking to himself, or the <mark>hastening of his steps</mark> which marks the climax of the fancied situation. <small> Sigmund Freud, <a name="SFCP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SFCP"><cite title="source">Collected Papers II</cite></a> (1924) 52</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15177i" href="c15all.htm#c15177i">VI.C.15:177(i)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
